FLAVORS OF THE WORLD
Wherever we fly around the globe, we have the enviable job
of tasting and savoring the cuisines of the world. We invite you
to share our discoveries while traveling with us.
ENTREES
FILET TIPS BORDELAISE
The chefs of Bordeaux, a region known for gastron-
omy and fine wines, are noted for their craftsmanship
in blending wines with classical sauces. These methods
are used to create this dish which combines choice
filet tips, shallots, mushrooms and herbs, all simmered
in a Bordeaux wine flavored Beef Stock. Accompanied
by spiced rice and honey coated carrots.
BAKED LUMACHE SHELL
This unusual Neopolitan dish contains Ricotta cheese
stuffed in a Lumache pasta shell. We bake it in a
meat sauce made from chopped beef, tomatoes and
seasonings, and present it with a delightful combina-
tion of Zucchini and Cauliflower.
BAKED CHICKEN, PLANTATION STYLE
From the deep South comes this unusual version of
Southern fried chicken. Our cooks take a boneless
Spring chicken breast, dip it in a cream batter and
roll it in buttery bread crumbs mixed with fresh herbs
and spices. Baked until golden brown, we serve it
with glazed yams and green beans with pimentos.
SALAD
GARDEN SALAD BOWL
Fresh garden greens in season tossed with an array of
crisp and colorful vegetables. garnished with
Garbanzo beans, tomato and jumbo ripe olive. Served
with our zesty Thousand Island Dressing.
THE SWEET COURSE
APPLE CHEESE TART
A smooth lemon flavored cream cheese filling topped
with tangy apples and spices, nested in a graham
cracker crust. Sprinkled with toasted almonds.
TWA's freshly brewed coffee
Tea
Sanka
Milk
Dinner Mint
If you have occasion to travel overseas, either to Europe, Africa,
Hawaii or across the Pacific, may we suggest you consider the con-
venience of TWA's Around the World Service. From East to West,
TWA flies to major world centers.
D-95
52
